{
  "stem": "22869.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They took away a whole detail from-- from-- from Auschwitz, and my brother was-- my older brother was one of them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we lost completely any kind of account on him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We thought that he's s gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, we had a live witness telling us that he saw him dead, but whatever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It turned out to-- to be a lie, but-- so my brother now was in contact with-- with my sister.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So sometimes we used to meet on the road.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I used to take some bread and some stuff and give him over, and he used to schlep it in the-- in the ladies' section.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we really became you know, like a-- like a little post office that would carry messages.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so you find out how our sister feels and some others.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We used to carry messages to other people who were in the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If somebody wanted to know, how's my sister, how's-- how's my brother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So this was like a little secret underground post office.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, we had to be very careful, because if they catch you, first of all, you lose your position, number one.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they probably would beat the dickens out of you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and-- and if not worse, I mean.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "How long did that continue?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That continued-- that continued till-- till the end of '44.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have to tell you one of the incidents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Since we were now in a camp where-- where we had almost everything to dispose that we wanted to have what people bring in.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we got a hold of a-- of a Jewish prayer shawl, of a tallis.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
